    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the beef mince is cooking, add the <strong>spaghetti</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>spaghetti</strong> for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite then drain and return to the pot until serving</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve the<strong> beef stock mix</strong>, <strong>Henderson’s Relish</strong> and <strong>soy sauce</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your<strong> stock</strong></p>",
